Azure DNS includes security features such as:

* Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)
* DNSSEC (Domain Name System Security Extensions)
* Activity logging

For example, DNSSEC protects against spoofing attacks.

# Real-life use case:
A real-life use case is securing domain records for financial applications.

# Real-life example::
Another example is controlling access to DNS zones using RBAC.

These features ensure secure domain management.
